cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

This paper is about deep unsupervised clustering using a variant of the Variational Autoencoder (VAE) called the Gaussian Mixture VAE (GMVAE) with discrete latent variables. The paper proposes a continuous relaxation of the discrete variables to reduce training time complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with deep unsupervised learning. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it uses the CIFAR-100 dataset, and natural language processing (cs.CL) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of the method for text data. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) as it uses a variant of the VAE.
